    "Reappraisal has been shown to be an effective way to reduce negative emotion in a variety of contexts: clinical (Aldao et al., 2010; Cohen & Ochsner, 2018), interpersonal (English et al., 2012; Sahi et al., 2023), and intergroup relations (Halperin et al., 2013; Pinus et al., 2025).",
    "Reappraisal skills can be learned and improved, and it can be taught with relative ease and EXPLORING HUMAN AND AI EMOTIONAL SUPPORT success (Cohen & Ochsner, 2018; Wang et al., 2020).",
    "Due to its simplicity and utility, reappraisal is a good candidate for LLMs for emotional support.",
    "In the past few years, there have been a few notable efforts to utilize LLMs for reappraisal.",
    "The primary efforts have been directed at providing a proof of concept (Reif et al., 2022; Zhan et al., 2024; Ziems et al., 2022)."
